review_data.content: Very nice dinner I had with my wife and my parents. The onion rings are very good and the spareribs are amazing.

If you like BBQ food especially ribs then you are in the correct place here. The food was excellent, I had the ribs and the meat just slid off the bone. Really good quality.
I also tried the spicy hot wings. They were also excellent, not too hot but tasty got. You could feel the almost Tabasco type spice but it was not overpowering and had a enjoyable taste.
Service was great and the interior was relaxing.

What an amazing place to hangout and grab a drink or meal. Overall great atmosphere, very friendly and attentive staff and very tasty food and selection of beverages. Will certainly come back during my next visit to Zurich

"Outback Platter" was great to get a taste of kangaroo, crocodile plus some classics with a twist, like cola glazed spare-ribs. My favourite was the roasted vegies, onion rings, chutney sauce and home made chips that came with this platter. Great Aussie desert menu too including pavlova. Extremely friendly and fabulous decor. Thanks a lot for a great treat.
The food was very nice. But the staff was slow, not very attentive, and forgot our dessert.

Great service, fast and super pleasant staff! Good job to the evening shift. Open until 23om on Sun, and serves very satisfying food. Their fries are a must, and they have a great selection of beer. Loved the decoration too, and great evening playlist for an Aussie vibe :)
Such a great place, with super attentive staff. Always the first choice for drinks and good food with my friend group!

I went to Aussie on a road trip for 4 months a couple of years ago and this restaurant remembered me this good moment. The food is nice, exactly like there. The ambiance is fun and friendly and the decoration is spot on. The only "downside" is that the restaurant is quite full, but I guess it's because it is good ;)

Totally different to everything in Zurich. More casual. Humour in the menu. And even some good Australian beers. Have a Coopers ( a family beer from before microbreweries made beer good again). Not cheap. But this is Zurich!

Fun place! Staff is great :)
The crocodile meat is real and tastes great!! ThTs why we came there haha

It’s a little dark, outside there is a fire pit! It’s awesome!
Have fun and enjoy butbyea ... 70 bucks for water and 1.5 dishes haha
It yea Zürich!

Fun atmosphere, although it can get a bit noisy. If the place is crowded the service can take a while. The food is super. Highly recommend chicken wings and the chicken club sandwich (full of yummy flavours). The potatoe chips taste amazing, the crispier the better.

Perfect place for a good and tasty food. The restaurant have as specific Australian food and drink. The location place is near the city center, close to the Zürich Lake. It is very easy to get there. The place have outdoor tables situated in a yard between  buildings. The nice part is that, no matter what you order, you get it in no longer than 5 minures. That's admirable if you consider the food diversity which is served here. The personnel is very kind and interested in how you feel and if you like the food.
Refreshing drinks, very good chicken. Also have options for vegetarian meals. Perfect for a summer dinner and right next to the station.

2 stars because quality seems to vary greatly, probably depending on who is working in the kitchen / at the bar:

+ great drinks in general, if they are made well
+ great food, especially the burger. Serving a bit too big for me, so if there was an option for a smaller one would be great, but it's delicious.

- We were there two weeks ago and there were plant louse on the salad! I didn't want to scare my friend so I didn't say anything, but the kitchen should check hygiene! I hope you actually wash the salad / vegetables (and hands etc....)
- Once we bought a cocktail but it was basically only fruit juice w/o alcohol (probably forgotten?). Fortunately, the staff was understanding enough to provide us with a shot instead.

Apart from that, the food and drinks

Well, what shall I say. It is an okay location. A typical place in Zurich where you pay for the name rather than for the food. I've been there for a gathering with friends and had a burger. The burger was not special at all. I am sure the meat is healthier than at big M but the taste was really average. The side dish was poor with a tiny container of coalslaw and some potato wedges. And yes the price was remarkable 25 Franks.
My colleagues ordered a shared platter with kangaroo, chicken and crocodile meat and got 2 tiny pieces each along some veggies and paid 42 Franks each. Honestly speaking it is not a place I would go back to.

This place is primarily known for its all-you-can-eat chicken wings, its ribs and its crocodile skewers but today I opted for their vegetarian tatar. I wasn't disappointed. Based on dried tomatoes and wheat, the dish was just as good as 'the real thing' and came with minced onions, pickled cucumber, capres, a spicy sour cream and of course toasted bread.
Very good food, mediocre service. In total a Good experience!

Aussie themed decor with some imported beers. Food is most definitely more pub than really Aussie (no chicken parma!) but it does have crocodile and kangaroo if you're brave enough. I had the ribs which was a huge portion - meat fell off the bone and they were tasty! Staff like most places in Zurich were multilingual and friendly

food was good but not for picky eaters .

Waitress was very rude as when she got the order wrong. she never replaced it due to, “that not being what she heard”
Been there several times. Authentic food and good drinks
Great place to go after work, good selection of beers and I love their burger :)
Nice place with good food and friendly stuff. During the weekend you should make a reservetion.
Food was actually very poor. Service was good though. Will, however, never go back.
Good food and very good service. I had the vegetarian burger with quinoa it was delicious. I recommend.
Staffs and service are pretty good. Food is very tasty especially crocodile & kangaroo  but it's a little bit expensive.
More candles than a catholic church! But fun nonetheless
Poor selection of beer and high prices.  The service though is friendly and efficient.  I just expected more as it’s a popular place in a good location
Great location and comfort food! Recommended.
Overall a good restaurant and good vibes. I just think they are not quite sure what “all you can eat” means…. Staff are not open to always help..
Very tasty food and fast staff 👍
Just amazing, extremely nice service, lovely! A hidden gem of Zürich
One of my favorite restaurants in Zurich! You have to try the fries, they are the best ever 😍
I have been there for Australia Day and it was awesome! Just the service was slow due to the amount of people in house I believe. Need to go back there to check it again ;)

Lovely place for both a drink and food. They have an interesting menu including kangaroo and crocodile and the food was quick. Typical Australian/British pub style. Had a good atmosphere and was also right by a train station.

The restaurant is brilliant: I just love how it is decorated and how friendly the staff is. The food itself amazes me every time. Prices are a bit higher but more than worth it. The only downside: The restaurant is a hotspot for eating and if you don’t reserve a table you might just have to wait. Also, it is rather loud in the evening.
Very delicious food! Enjoyed the meal a lot 😍 Will come back soon.

This place is packed so they don't really need my review but for my taste the food is mediocre at best and it is way way way too loud. If you want to get drunk after work, it's a good choice. But if you want to have dinner and a conversation, steer clear.

Apparently people are making very different experiences here. We received our order within 5 min and the bill within 1 min, even though the place was full. And yes it's noisy when full, but crowds can be loud, that's not unexpected in a place like this. The waiters weren't rude. The food was really very good. Would visit again.

Great tasting food, the chicken wings were delicious, but the potato wedges (I think they're the 'down under fries' ) we're so good. Definitely within the top 5 fries I've ever tasted!
The atmosphere is nice, not exactly stereotypical Australian, but it goes for its own theme.

One downside though, according to them a sharing platter of chicken wings, for two people, is only 6 wings. I would've liked more, especially since they taste real good.
Good place for some spare ribs. Casual dining but gets busy during weekends.

First I would like to mention that the service was very good. Allan was very attentive and friendly.

The food was however very disappointing.
Mixed plate of crocodile and kangaroo turned out to be a plate of boiled parsnips and carrots. Papadums and dal on top got us confused.
Loads of fried and soggy potatoes.
The small pieces of kangaroo meat was really sour and smelly so we decided to feed it to our hungry dog under the table that hadn't been eating for 12 hours. She wouldn't go near it.

Outback should get motivated and qualified staff for the kitchen and work with fresh food for the prices they have.

Food and drinks decent but expensive(hence 2stars) and service absolutely horrendous !

Yesterday was my second time eating here. Both times we came for the all you can eat wings (somewhat expensive but hey, it's Switzerland). The first time was alright, fries pretty good, chicken decent but not very hot for hot wings. The only problem was that our waitress kept forgetting our order and we had to wait an hour for our food to arrive, then another lengthy time for the "seconds" and "thirds" of the all you can eat. No problem though, it was busy and we understood.
However, yesterday we encountered the worst service I think I have ever had. The Waitress (different one from the first) belittled us for not finishing every last bite of our all you can eat chicken - raising her voice at us, arguing and talking down to us like children! When we left the change from our bill as a small (and definitely undeserved) tip, she sarcastically retorted "thank you sooooo much". Definitely not coming back and wouldn't recommend it either.

I went with five friends and we ordered the all you can eat wings. In past experience, I have been to "all you can eat" places that serve shockingly little food and at a slow rate; this was not the case at Outback, and our food was brought quickly, both in the first and second round of wings. Although the price is quite high, when you consider how many wings you can eat and the prices of similar size dishes, you actually are saving money, so I appreciate that the dish size is well calculated.
A great place to hang out with your mates before a night out. With a large variety of different beers to pick from. Food menu is decent for a bar but filling. Great for anyone who's 18+

Outback was great. I came all the way from Outback Steakhouse in America just to compared and it was aight. Jeannette was an excellent hostess and most definitely deserves praise for her great work and accommodation.
Top for having lots of wings especially on all you can eat Monday. Great beers, good pricing. Lighting is a little too dim fjr me, but apart from that service, food and location are great.

The bar and atmosphere are fine. Good location and nice staff. A bit pricy though. Loved the monster truck burger but it was served on paper, which is not the best thing to eat on with a knife. Also PLEASE do your own burger meat! Stop buying the ones already spiced :(( the desserts are nice. Though the choice of meals is very limited, not sure I will go back there.
good quality. nice staff. visited as a group of 7. orders came in due time.
The food is good, service is slow. There is no kids menu.

Came in for the Monday Unlimited chicken with a couple of friends and I enjoyed every bit of it. The chicken was just right and I look forward to coming back once the portion I had fully digests. Would however like to have some extra sauces on the side to have with the chicken and potato wedges
Excellent! Very cozy place.

GREATEST. FRIES. EVER. I deadass go to this place at least once a week for the fries from.down under. The atmosphere and staff are great. Its hard to get a seat on the terrace when the weather is nice tho..

Nice cross between a tradional pub and a restaurant hence the 'Outback Lodge' name.  I have eaten at Outbacks in Los Angeles and Sao Paulo and there the restaurants have very good food but tend to be expensive/less value for money compared to other chains.  In Zurich, where every restaurant meal is expensive, this down side is eliminated.   There are vegan and vegetarian options on the menu which are very tasty.  Recommend this place.

We ate Kangaroo. The meat was good but the sauce tasted like prodega, as well as the bohnen, kinda like cafeteria. Beer at 8 CHF so ok for Zürich, many beers on the Australian menu were not available. Slow in general. Waitress was friendly though. Overall I expected something different, maybe Australian but was a bit Swiss German.

The service was terrible. We went on an all you could eat day and were shouted at by the waitress for not eating enough. The worst part was that she had told us how many wings she was brining us instead of asking. The chips were good and the wings were okay but that was all.

Fun place for after work drink and pub grub though don't expect much more than chips with exotic meat (that's the USP) and overpriced beer (that's a Zurich speciality).  A bit cramped - service is decent, prompt and more or less friendly - By the train station so quick getaway possible - Probably better pubs in town but certainly should be visited at least once
Nice location, friendly staff and easy to get there by public transportation. Staff is super friendly, food is not really healthy but i like it

Good food for a reasonable price. It took quite a bit (about 50 minutes) until our food arrived and the waitress forgot a coke, but overall we were treated quite friendly. I’d recommend this place if you’re not in a hurry :).

Very nice service lady.
The wineglas was chipped - ordered a new one - and it was chipped again.
The peppermint tea is served as a glas of hot water and two stems of pepermint.

The food was great.
must try potato wedges and onion rings

Nice cozy place to sit outside and have a beer. Service is really sometimes good sometimes bad, which indicated the incompetency of the management team. More trainings to the employees is needed. Food was okay.... just a bit oily in my opinion.

Fighting to get served when there is only one member of staff is unpleasant. Staff usually indifferent to customers although this is common in Zürich. Not a great range of drinks and no happy hour offers. Underwhelming.

Met new friend for a beer- $17 for the 2 I think:( local guy next to me knocked over candle and spilled wax all over me, but he was nice and apologetic enough... regular but nice 'downtown' bar. I didn't have the food.
Food was good. Interesting and enlighting literature available next to the table. Was a great experience. Service was a bit slow sometimes.
Great place to drink on a Friday evening. Quite a great selection and quality, but I would recommend to sink the prices to attract even more customers

The staff was nice until I paid... I took a simple coffee and had to pay 4.80 CHF (which is already on the expensive side...). The server asked me if I needed my change over 5 CHF which is, after me, not how we proceed, but I left the tip. I would have left it anyway but more happily if it hadn't been asked... Too bad because it makes a bad impression.

The Outback is great! It‘s perfect to meet friends and drink something! The Barkeepers are very nice and make delicious drinks!
Can recommend to everyone:)
Good atmosphere but extremely noisy. Difficult to have a conversation in the main part of the bar. Service is good and very friendly.
Always a pleasure to eat @ the outback. Food is fresh, portions are large, staff busy but friendly. You typically need to book in advance, as it is quite packed at times.
Nice place, good food and reasonable prices considering it is in Zürich. Would have given five stars if the noise level would have been a bit lower. After all, conversation is essential when dining.

Nice place but horrible service.
With the place less than half full on a Sunday evening, we waited more than half an hour and we did not even get all of our drinks.
The waiter rudely talking to us then made us leave the place.

Thanks but, no thanks.
Great food, wonderful atmosphere for a birthday party. Staff was friendly and spoke fluent english which is always nice!  Would definitely go back.

Terrible place. We reserved a table, but we had to wait anyway 50minutes outside before being able to seat. Waiters unfriendly and overall just avarage place to spend a couple of hours if you cannot go anywhere else. Avoid it if you can

The food was OK, but we were ripped off with the water. Paid CHF 29 (!!!) for 2 liters of water. I guess it was our own fault for ordering all-you-can-eat chicken wings on Chicken Wings Monday, which they advertise everywhere. They seem to cross-finance this from very, very expensive drinks.

This Australian concept bar and restaurant is located at the Stadelhofen train station, only 5 walking minutes away from the lake of Zurich and the picturesque old town the locals call "Niederdörfli"
I love the ambiente - at first you think you are sitting outside but you are actually inside.
If you want to try crocodile, kangaroo or ostrich, this ist the place to go. They also offer Aussie beer.
Good place to trink 💦

Delicious!!
Their signature wings are 10/10 perfect
The only thing is that all meat had an element of pork in it, so their meat is not suitable for Muslims

Food was OK, but nothing to write home about (i.e. good but not special). The "Outback Killer", advertised as being perfect for meat lovers, consisted of two rather small lamb chops, two or three cubes of kangaroo and a few slices of chorizo with some vegetables in between. The patato wedges were good, but a rather small serving. The ambiente is also not really my thing - thrift shop furnishing is probably very authentic, but my chair was rather uncomfortable which is unfortunate, as we had to wait quite a while for the food. And then there's the noise. It's so bad you can barely understand your immediate neighbors.
And all that for prices on the high end (typical for Zürich City).
Free starter at lunches. Unlimited chicken wings for set price on Monday evenings. Very good food. Pretty low prices for a restaurant in Zürich.
Great atmosphere for a quick drink or 2, but it can get noisy. Better in the summer, one can sit outside, inside it can get very noisy. Did I mention noisy?
It had excellent service, fresh food, good variety! Also beautiful outside  sitting! Food is yummy!

Lovely pub/restaurant with an Australian theme. You can get crocodile skewers there as well as normal burgers and steaks.
For a quick after work beer it's good. It is directly next to the trains and you can't miss your train, unless you have too much fun talking to the interesting guests.
great beer selection and friendly service
Best Chicken Wings of my life. Once in a while I will yearn outback chicken wings and I've never left disappointed. Also, try the wedges - they're awesome.
Not impressed, food is ok but service sucks. Orders are forgotten, took 20 min and 3 reminders to get a bill. Also 34 for 12 wings is pricey for such simple pub food.
Great food, good lunch menu too. Chickenwings all-you-can-eat on a Monday Night's a favourite. Service can be slow.
Uncomplicated aussie bar, been pretty quiet due to covid. Fairly high prices for cocktail, nothing unusual for zürich tho.
Love the burgers and the beer selection. Very crowded on weekends, so make a reservation. One of the few places in zurich to go with a larger group!

Very interesting choice of food, have even kangaroo and crocodile meat ! But mostly chicken which is absolutely delicious. Strangely enough, not that expensive.
Classic aussie / pub style food. Very friendly service. Come here on Mondays for the all you can eat chicken wings.
